Tr67844.@label: Fig. 2.  Consensus phylogram (50 % majority rule) of 17 222 trees resulting from a Bayesian analysis of the combined seven loci sequence alignment using MrBayes v. 3.2.1. Bayesian posterior probabilities values are indicated on their respective branches and the scale bar indicates 0.2 expected changes per site. The tree was rooted to Readeriella mirabilis (Teratosphaeriaceae) (CBS 125000).
